item.description:
The other day I started a remote powershell session with Invoke-Command and my script ran&hellip;
and ran&hellip;
and ran&hellip;
I finally tired of waiting, so I decided that I&rsquo;d RDP in and get the information via. GUI, but the server was sluggish. This isn&rsquo;t an underspec&rsquo;ed server where routine use might cause a small but noticable performance hit. I took a look at taskman and saw the wsmprovhost.exe process consuming 50/64GB RAM.
